9. Lambda Developer Notes
Parsing. With raw message delivery enabled, the SQS record body is the JSON payload itself. Keep an envelope fallback, and never let a non-JSON body crash the function — during rollout, contact points that still use the old default template will send plain text:
def parse_body(body: str) -> dict | None:
    try:
        payload = json.loads(body)
    except json.JSONDecodeError:
        log.warning("Non-JSON alert body, skipping (old template?)")
        return None   # or route to a DLQ for inspection
    # Fallback if raw message delivery is off (SNS envelope)
    if isinstance(payload, dict) and payload.get("Type") == "Notification":
        try:
            payload = json.loads(payload["Message"])
        except json.JSONDecodeError:
            log.warning("Non-JSON Message in SNS envelope, skipping")
            return None
    return payload
